welcome to nishamadhulika.com

00:00:07.349 --> 00:00:12.126
today we will make matar paneer which is liked by almost everyone.

00:00:12.537 --> 00:00:18.330
let's see what all ingerdients are required for making matar paneer.

00:00:18.773 --> 00:00:20.908
paneer - 400 grams

00:00:21.219 --> 00:00:24.283
peas  - 500 grams

00:00:24.753 --> 00:00:33.280
paste - 3-4 tomatoes,2 green chilly and 1 inch ginger piece

00:00:33.757 --> 00:00:35.749
cumin seeds - 1/2 tsp

00:00:36.053 --> 00:00:37.243
asafoetida - 1 pinch

00:00:37.492 --> 00:00:40.938
malai - 3 tbsp (whisked)

00:00:41.216 --> 00:00:44.710
salt - as per taste (3/4 tsp)

00:00:44.935 --> 00:00:47.364
turmeric powder - 1/2 tsp

00:00:47.717 --> 00:00:50.058
coriander powder - 1 tsp

00:00:50.338 --> 00:00:53.807
red chilly powder - less then 1/4 tsp

00:00:54.232 --> 00:00:57.414
garam masala - less then 1/4 tsp

00:00:58.258 --> 00:01:00.790
green coriander - 1 tbsp (finely chopped)

00:01:01.126 --> 00:01:02.634
oil - for making sabzi

00:01:04.210 --> 00:01:08.004
for making sabzi fry peas first.

00:01:08.230 --> 00:01:13.190
add 1/2 tbsp oil in pan.

00:01:13.894 --> 00:01:21.638
add peas in pan and fry until they get tender.

00:01:23.324 --> 00:01:27.879
cover and cook for 2 minutes so that they get cooked quickly.

00:01:37.702 --> 00:01:45.595
peas are ready; take them out in a bowl.

00:01:52.170 --> 00:01:54.344
fry paneer as well.

00:01:54.902 --> 00:01:59.695
for this add 1/2 tbsp oil in pan.

00:02:07.773 --> 00:02:10.281
place the paneer chunks in pan for frying.

00:02:11.749 --> 00:02:18.246
cut paneer into any size of your preference.

00:02:21.837 --> 00:02:26.869
fry until they turn little brown in color.

00:02:27.536 --> 00:02:30.980
meanwhile prepare gravy.

00:02:31.286 --> 00:02:39.584
for this add 2 tbsp oil in pan.

00:02:50.497 --> 00:03:05.644
when oil get hot add cumin seeds,asafoetida,turmeric powder,coriander powder,tomto-chilly-ginger paste.

00:03:12.083 --> 00:03:20.333
saute masala until oil starts floating on the surface.

00:03:24.007 --> 00:03:26.436
flip the sides of paneer.

00:03:45.784 --> 00:03:51.403
keep stirring the masala else it might stick to the pan.

00:03:58.274 --> 00:04:03.012
paneer is roasted now take it out.

00:04:10.371 --> 00:04:13.570
fry rest of the paneer chunks.

00:04:19.166 --> 00:04:25.217
masala is ready;now we will add cream into it.

00:04:25.698 --> 00:04:31.436
saute the masala until oil starts floating on the surface.

00:04:33.173 --> 00:04:39.205
wehave prepared tomato and cream gravy for this sabzi.

00:04:39.425 --> 00:04:50.426
gravy can be prepared with curd,poppy seeds,cashew nuts,coconut,sesame seeds,gram flour,corn flour and so on.

00:04:50.795 --> 00:04:58.423
for better understanding and knowledge about gravies log on to nishamadhulika.com

00:04:58.858 --> 00:05:04.255
prepare gravy as per your preference.

00:05:04.554 --> 00:05:07.007
masala is ready .

00:05:10.074 --> 00:05:25.178
now add water as per your preference or 1-1.5 cups.

00:05:28.985 --> 00:05:33.985
when gravy starts boiling add peas and paneer into it.

00:05:41.242 --> 00:06:00.327
gravy has started boiling now add salt,fried peas and paneer into it.

00:06:04.262 --> 00:06:16.889
add all ingredients,cover and cook for 2 minutes so that all spices get aborbed in the spices.

00:06:23.544 --> 00:06:29.956
sabzi is ready and is smelling heaven

00:06:30.305 --> 00:06:33.987
now add green coriander in the sabzi.

00:06:40.503 --> 00:06:41.781
turn off the gas.

00:06:43.215 --> 00:06:45.628
tempting matar paneer sabzi is ready.

00:06:45.956 --> 00:06:53.303
we have used 400 grams and 500 grams peas for making this sabzi.

00:06:53.582 --> 00:06:57.725
this much quantity can be served to 4-5 family members.

00:06:58.286 --> 00:07:03.818
serve matar paneer sabzi with chapatti,parantha,naan or rice.

